[code:1nd6aw4o]define variable &lt;health&gt;
type numeric
value &lt;100&gt;
scope local
display &lt;Health&#58; !&gt;
onchange if &#40; %health&#91;userid&#93;% &lt;= 0 &#41; then msg &lt;You are unconcious!&gt;
end define[/code:1nd6aw4o]To enter this via QDK, simply add a new variable and each feild enter the apropiate data. the onchange is a 'condition' of camparing values (heath and 0). But it'll be much simply to just add it in a text editer, by opening the game, finding where the variables go (create a 'dummy' variable to test where they go if you don't know) and pasting this in.
